<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
The presence of hairs on the eyes is variable in 
<taxonomicName box="[782,933,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Ruizantheda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[782,933,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Ruizantheda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it is here understood, similarly to the variation present in 
<taxonomicName box="[390,620,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Pseudagapostemon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[390,620,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Pseudagapostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hairs are conspicuous in 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1071,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Ruizantheda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis box="[939,1071,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">R. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, weak in 
<taxonomicName box="[1188,1344,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Ruizantheda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divaricata">
<emphasis box="[1188,1344,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">R. divaricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Ruizantheda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">R. centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no distinct hairs. 
